# Phase 4 Walkthrough: Live Interview Interface

I have successfully executed Phase 4 and built the core recording interface.

## What was built

1. **Questions API**: Added `generateQuestions` endpoint logic to dynamically provide randomized questions based on the selected interview type (HR, Technical, Company, Resume, Mixed). 
2. **Answers API**: Integrated `multer` in the backend to handle `multipart/form-data` uploads. We successfully set up local `video/webm` blob storage in the `backend/uploads` directory (accessible statically).
3. **Live Interview Interface (`LiveInterviewPage.jsx`)**:
    - **Camera Stream**: Taps into `navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia` using a large, mirrored `<video>` preview.
    - **MediaRecorder logic**: Configured to capture `video/webm` blobs when answering. Included the placeholder logic (`// ── AI MODEL INTEGRATION SLOT`) where WebSocket data will be streamed directly to your FastAPI python services in real-time.
    - **Controls**: Built the timer (default 2-minute limit), start, and stop buttons.
    - **Question display**: Fetches questions and advances one by one until completed.
4. **Processing Screen**: Implemented the beautiful rotating AI coach loading screen with shimmering progress bars that the user sees while their interview is being "processed".

## Verification 

- **Backend**: Both `questions.js` and `answers.js` routers are successfully wired into `app.js`. The server compiles correctly (`APP_OK`).
- **Frontend**: The `interviewApi` handles `FormData` correctly. Vite `npm run build` succeeds perfectly.

## Next Steps

If you are ready, run `/gsd-plan-phase 5` to tackle the AI Analysis Services setup (Python microservices structure and integration).
